arStrings.szText: Attempting to divert attention away from him, to the person who's just walked up to join the conversation. (The "(hic)" is a drunken hiccup.)
Hey, you look at me! I'm not done talking to you.
Trying to get the attention of a man she's in the middle of reprimanding.
I'm looking at you. You're... uh, as radiant as a ... Backwater sunset.
Sugary sweet, condescending. (Backwater - where they live - is a shithole; being compared to its sunset isn't much of a compliment.)
This is serious shit, Tomaj. We both know there are more and more Drowned sightings every day.
Stern, exasperated, trying to get the man to whom she's speaking to talk her seriously, stop joking around.
Look (hic) sweetheart, I'll do the work. Cross my heart.
Sugary sweet, condescending. (The "(hic)" is a drunken hiccup.)
Damn right, you will. Or the next time I see you, I'm going straight to the boss.
Exasperated, threatening. Trying to get the man to whom she's speaking to talk her seriously, stop joking around.
Hey! You... you're not from around here, are you? Listen - you help me out, I can help you survive in this place.
A bit sly, like "Heyyyy." He's in hot water and hoping this newcomer can help him get out of trouble.
Help me find any new bodies that have washed ashore. Check 'em for anything we could use, then I'll burn them.
And grab any extra salvage we find along the way (hic), got it?
Informative, with a light tone. (The "(hic)" is a drunken hiccup.)
